at.irian.ankor.system

Class AnkorSystem

  • java.lang.Object
    • at.irian.ankor.system.AnkorSystem

  • public class AnkorSystem
extends java.lang.Object
    This is the main system object that sticks all the Ankor parts together. Typically every node in an Ankor environment has exactly one AnkorSystem instance. So, in a pure-Java client-server environment (e.g. JavaFX client and Java web server) there is one AnkorSystem instance on the client side and one AnkorSystem instance on the server side.
